<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.64.29" />

<fw type="curatorial">29</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street<lb/>
Lincoln, Nebraska 68505<lb/>
November 16, 1972
</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Dr. Ruth Crone</addrLine>
<addrLine>Apartment 53</addrLine>
<addrLine>418 South 38th Avenue</addrLine>
<addrLine>Omaha, Nebraska 68131</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Dr. Crone:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I was glad to hear from you, and I greatly appreciate what you say about my little book, <hi rend="caps">ALL IS BUT A BEGINNING</hi>.</p>

<p>You ask me to send you my signature for a copy of my book which you are presenting to Marion Marsh Brown.</p>

<p>I am sending a copy of the Flaming Rainbow referred to in Black Elk's great vision. I was named for this rainbow by Black Elk, and we have used it as a book plate for the first 500 copies of my book. I hope this will be satisfactory for your purpose.</p>
<closer>
<salute>With all kind thoughts,</salute>


<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>

<note>JGN:nh</note>
</closer>

</div1>
</body>

